src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website adapts well to smaller screens with large clear text and perfectly scaled images. Unlike most mobile sites, the hamburger menu is placed in the center of the top menu but also disappears as soon as users start scrolling down the page. Since more scrolling is required, the lack of a sticky menu is more noticeable.</p><p>Like the desktop site, the mobile website received a perfect score for SEO and best practices on the PageSpeed Insights test but scored 45/100 for performance.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="granite-hill-lodge-campground" class="entry-website-title">Granite Hill Lodge &amp; Campground</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-granite-hill-20240526-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-granite-hill-20240526-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-granite-hill-20240526-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Granite Hill Lodge &amp; Campground"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.granitehillny.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.granitehillny.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Fort Ann, New York, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Granite Hill Lodge &amp; Campground is a family- and pet-friendly campsite nestled between the sprawling Adirondack Mountains. The campsite offers tented camping, electrified RV sites, a cozy cabin, and a lodge.</p><p>Granite Hill is one of the few campsite websites that do not have a direct booking button on the home page. The site would also benefit from a downloadable campsite map and directions to the campsite. However, it includes an FAQ page, blog, and a section for local attractions.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>WAVE only picked up a few contrast errors on the site. The website has a dedicated blog page with interesting information about the campsite and related regions. There is a page for local attractions and FAQs.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>There is no booking button on the home page which seems like a massive oversite for people who want to quickly find and book accomodation. The website does not mention sustainability practices or accessibility options.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-granite-hill-20240526-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-granite-hill-20240526-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The large background images of the Adirondacks and campsite photos look spectacular on larger screens. The desktop site also provides space for the images of the cabin and lodge to grab attention. The top menu provides easy navigation but does not stay in place as you scroll. This could be fixed with a sticky menu or a back-to-top button.</p><p>The desktop website received a performance score of 71/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights test.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-granite-hill-20240526-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-granite-hill-20240526-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile website does well to retain the aesthetic of the desktop site with extended images and easily readable text. As with the desktop site, the top hamburger menu disappears as you scroll down the page, making it difficult to navigate to the rest of the site.</p><p>The mobile website scored 40/100 on the PageSpeed Insights test, indicating slower response times.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="detach-primitive" class="entry-website-title">Detach Primitive</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-detach-primitive-20240526-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-detach-primitive-20240526-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-detach-primitive-20240526-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Detach Primitive"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.godetach.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.godetach.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Rockford, Michigan, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Detach Primitive is an off-grid campsite and retreat designed for relaxation and outdoor activities. Situated in the forest of Rockford, Michigan, it offers unique accommodations such as tipis, yurts, an underground hobbit home, and A-frame structures.</p><p>The Detach Primitive website uses attention-grabbing images and short descriptive text blocks instead of lengthy information pages. This provides a good snapshot of the campsite but makes the website feel slightly disjointed. While some pertinent information is missing, notable features of the website include the bio page and packing lists.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website includes a packing list to help prepare visitors since the site is off-grid. There is an option to purchase gift cards from a convenient link on the home page. The "About" page includes a bio of the team and press links.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>Pricing is not mentioned anywhere on the website which might put off visitors. The website does not mention accessibility, sustainability, or a pet policy. WAVE picked up a few contrast errors on the site.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-detach-primitive-20240526-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-detach-primitive-20240526-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The widescreen background images feel distracting on larger screens, but the side profile images work better to create a balanced aesthetic. The desktop site has a sticky top menu and a prominent "Book Now" button for quick navigation and the site loaded quickly in our real-world tests.</p><p>The desktop website performed well on Google's PageSpeed Insights test with a performance score of 89/100. It scored 100/100 for accessibility and best practices.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-detach-primitive-20240526-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-detach-primitive-20240526-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>On smaller screens, the background images seem less distracting, creating a more refined text-to-image ratio. The top menu converts to a sticky hamburger menu but loses the prominent "Book Now" CTA which could easily have fitted in the center of the field.</p><p>The mobile website received a score of 44/100 on PageSpeed Insights; however, in our real-world tests, we felt the mobile site had reasonable loading times.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
